# Code Conventions

## Components

- Functional components + hooks ONLY (no class components)
- Props type: `{ComponentName}Props`
- Named exports only (no default exports)
- Colocated tests: `ComponentName.test.tsx`

## TypeScript

- Strict mode — no `any`, no `@ts-ignore`
- Prefer `type` over `interface` for simple types; for React components, that includes the props alias `{ComponentName}Props` (use `interface` only when declaration merging or extending an external interface requires it)
- Import types: `import type { X } from "..."`

## Files

- kebab-case for files: `element-utils.ts`
- PascalCase for components: `LayerUI.tsx`

## How to verify

1. From the repo root, run `yarn test:typecheck` after substantive edits under `packages/**/*.ts(x)`.
2. On new or heavily touched components under `packages/`, confirm `export default` is not used for the component module and the props type is named `*Props`.
3. Confirm filenames: non-component modules use kebab-case; React component files use PascalCase; a colocated `ComponentName.test.tsx` exists when you add or substantially change a component.
